---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Thanuka Perera" description="Computer Science undergraduate and open-source builder from Colombo, Sri Lanka.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="wrap">
    <nav class="breadcrumb"><span>About</span></nav>
    <header class="detail-head">
      <span class="detail-topic">About</span>
      <h1 class="detail-title">Thanuka Perera</h1>
      <p class="detail-summary">Computer Science undergraduate and open-source builder from Colombo, Sri Lanka.</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm a second-year CS student at the University of Westminster (via IIT, Colombo), but most
        of what I know I've learned by building things and shipping them. I work across the
        stack — cloud-native backends, systems-level tooling in Rust and C++, and AI that runs
        entirely on-device — usually on a laptop with a 4&nbsp;GB GPU that forces me to be honest
        about performance.
      </p>
      <h2>What I care about</h2>
      <p>
        The low-level details other people skip: binary formats, cache behaviour, the difference
        between a tool that works and one that feels instant. I treat <strong>latency as a
        feature</strong>, I write tests for things I could get away with not testing, and I'd
        rather publish an honest negative result than a hyped claim that doesn't survive a bigger
        sample size.
      </p>
      <h2>Right now</h2>
      <p>
        Building <strong>shrinkray</strong> (reversible texture compression for game installs),
        <strong> Diana</strong> (a local-first voice assistant), and contributing to open-source
        projects. Long-term, I want to work on the kind of enterprise platforms and developer
        infrastructure that real systems are built on.
      </p>
      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:thanukasehasnaperera@gmail.com">thanukasehasnaperera@gmail.com</a>,
        find my code on <a href="https://github.com/Thanukamax">GitHub</a>, the bigger picture on
        my <a href="https://thanukamax.github.io">portfolio</a>, or connect on
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/thanuka-perera-889240337"> LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
